The paper deals with the problem of parameter learning in probabilistic graphical models, which is a common topic in machine learning. The use of Markov Chains and stochastic approximation theory suggests that the paper may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also proposes a new learning algorithm, which involves optimization techniques, indicating that it may also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks and optimization techniques further suggests that the paper may fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also deals with the problem of computational intractability, which is a common issue in information theory, suggesting that it may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper deals with real-world datasets, indicating that it may also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
